	(186,'Cloud Gardens','9N07GS0HCNPK',0,1,'Family & kids','cloud-gardens','Noio Games','/storage/games/images/cloud-gardens/cloud-gardens-prewie.jpeg','/storage/games/images/cloud-gardens/cloud-gardens-art.jpeg','/storage/games/images/cloud-gardens/cloud-gardens-title.jpeg','Harness the power of nature to overgrow lo-fi scenes of urban decay and manufactured landscapes. Create small plant-covered dioramas of brutalism and beauty by planting seeds, repurposing hundreds of discarded objects and creating unique structures for nature to reclaim.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDive into a relaxing sandbox mode with no goals, or take on a multi-chapter “campaign” where the task is to strike a balance between the natural and the manufactured. Adding objects will encourage lush vegetation to grow, but each object must be covered in foliage in order to proceed.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCloud Gardens hovers somewhere in between a sandbox toy and a game with challenges. Partly a gardening simulator, partly a dystopian landscape builder, and partly a puzzle game that is both satisfying and without frustration. It is a relaxing experience that takes you from one scene to the next while encouraging creativity and coming up with your own solutions.','2021-09-01 00:00:00',0,0,1,X'7B224361706162696C697479346B223A207B2274797065223A2022737570706F72745F346B222C2022737461747573223A20747275657D2C2022737570706F72743630667073223A207B2274797065223A2022737570706F72745F3630667073222C2022737461747573223A20747275657D7D',0,X'5B22656E222C20227A682D68616E73222C20227A682D68616E74222C20226672222C20226465222C20226A61222C20227074222C20226573222C20226974225D',4.50,0,0,0,0,0,0,2.55,2.55,0.00,'2021-09-09 18:23:34','2021-09-09 18:35:51'),
